rgy</a><span> or something equally magical.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"col=
or: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;">Real estate may be an even better bet. Landlords have contractual owners=
hip of their properties, and both humans and GPUs need a place to live. Eve=
n if AGI and its robots lower prices by building more housing and data cent=
ers, the humans who own land will be better positioned than most.&#160;</p>=
<p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>Mining</strong><span> may be the most defensible =
industry of all. As long as there is a demand for physical things, there wi=
ll be demand for the raw materials from which those things are made. Energy=
 generation and storage require critical metals, as do the data centers tha=
t our AGI overlords will call home. And like landlords, miners contractuall=
y own the right to mine their discoveries.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"colo=
