ew levels of human civilization, but new ways to mine and make even more me=
tals.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Mining&#8217;s progression has been an evo=
lution, but if you had to pick a date for the birth of modern mining, you m=
ight pick 1867, when Alfred Nobel, the Nobel Prize guy, discovered dynamite=
=2E&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54,=20=
55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Dynamite let miners blast through hard rock sa=
