dding-left: 4px;"><strong>OpEx: </strong><span>expenses to run the mine, in=
cluding labor, energy, materials, equipment maintenance, and logistics to g=
et the metals to market.&#160;</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 =
32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; colo=
r: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-b=
ottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>Refining&#160; &amp; Processing Costs=
:</strong><span> turning the raw material into marketable form by separatin=
g and purifying the valuable metals from the rock and dirt it comes up in.&=
#160;</span></p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The price of the metal is somew=
hat out of the miner&#8217;s control, although miners can choose to sit on =
deposits until prices rise to the point at which it becomes profitable to m=
ine it. Everything else is within the control of the miner, and miners choo=
se to mine deposits based on a number of factors that impact their profitab=
ility.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Those factors include:</p><ul style=3D"ma=
rgin-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-fo=
rmat: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); =
font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-le=
ft: 4px;"><strong>Size of the Deposit:</strong><span> The volume or tonnage=
 of the ore body is crucial because it determines the life of the mine and =
economies of scale, and thus how much capital the miner can invest in the s=
ite. Explorers and developers determine this by drilling a lot of holes inc=
reasingly far from the initial hole to determine how wide and deep the depo=
sit is during feasibility, and miners confirm this with their own team of g=
eologists.&#160;</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-spec=
ial-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55,=
 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padd=
ing-left: 4px;"><strong>Grade of Ore:</strong><span> This is the concentrat=
ion of the valuable mineral or metal within the ore, typically measured as =
a percentage or in grams per ton (g/t). Higher grades are better, because t=
hey reduce OpEx, refining and processing costs, and environmental impact.&#=
160;</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: =
bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4p=
x;"><strong>Depth of Deposit: S</strong><span>hallow deposits are generally=
 cheaper and safer to mine, often suitable for open-pit mining. Deep deposi=
ts require more complex and expensive underground mining techniques, increa=
sing CapEx and OpEx.</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-=
special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54,=
 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; =
padding-left: 4px;"><strong>Accessibility and Infrastructure:</strong><span=
> Proximity to roads, power sources, and ports reduces transportation and e=
nergy costs. Remote locations typically mean the miner has to run their own=
 roads and power, increasing CapEx and OpEx. The Biden Administration is </=
span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/18ca28cc-8a85-48a0-ab2b-27e4c=
3e0a536?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU"=
 rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">spending=
 $2.3 billion on an African railway</a><span> to get critical metals out of=
 Zambia.&#160;</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-specia=
l-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 5=
5); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; paddin=
g-left: 4px;"><strong>Political, Regulatory, and Environmental: </strong><s=
pan>Political stability is crucial to the long-term viability of a mine; yo=
u don&#8217;t want to spend hundreds of millions of dollars only to have a =
new regime kick you out of their country. Getting permits and approvals can=
 be more or less expensive, time-consuming, and existential depending on th=
e environmental impact and local regulatory environment.&#160;</span></p></=
li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=
=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>Capit=
al: </strong><span>These are expensive projects that often require dedicate=
d project financing, and the cost (and availability) of capital is a key le=
ver on profitability.</span><strong>&#160;</strong></p></li></ul><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;"><span>Whew. I just threw a lot at you, but each thing I listed is=
 crucial to understanding whether a mine will be profitable, and therefore,=
 how valuable a given discovery might be for a company like Earth AI. </spa=
n><strong>The ideal discovery is a large, high-grade deposit, close to the =
surface, in a politically stable and regulatorily friendly locale with easy=
 access to infrastructure.&#160;</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55,=
 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Some challen=
ges facing less-than-ideal deposits are being addressed by technology: meth=
ods to dig deeper more cheaply, automation, and better processing and refin=
ing. But the easiest way to make a mine profitable is just to discover more=
 ideal mines and prove more quickly that they&#8217;re ideal, which is wher=
e Earth AI is focusing.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Earth AI is an </span><s=
trong>Explorer</strong><span>. Understanding where that fits into the minin=
g industry value chain is the last bit of mining background we&#8217;ll nee=
d to dig into before we get to the Earth AI story.&#160;</span></p><h3 clas=
