posits and then either sell the property or partner with larger mining comp=
anies to develop the resource.&#160;</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8p=
x 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); fo=
nt-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left=
: 4px;"><strong>Developers:</strong><span> These companies have identified =
a mineral deposit and are working on developing it into a mine. They may be=
 in the process of securing permits, financing, and constructing the necess=
ary infrastructure to begin mining operations.</span></p></li><li style=3D"=
margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 5=
5, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; pa=
dding-left: 4px;"><strong>Producers:</strong><span> These are mining compan=
ies with anywhere from one to multiple operating mines generating revenue. =
Mid-Tier Producers might operate one or a few mines, and focus on a particu=
lar region or metal. Major Producers are global, operating tens of mines ac=
ross a diverse portfolio of assets, and can reach market capitalizations ex=
ceeding $10 or even $100 billion. Examples include companies like BHP, Rio =
Tinto, and Vale.&#160;</span></p></li></ol><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 5=
5); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">There is also =
a flotilla of ancillary companies that supports the industry with tools, se=
rvices, and money.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>Royalty and Streaming=
 Companies </strong><span>provide financing to mining companies in exchange=
 for a share of the revenue or a portion of the mineral production from the=
 mine. Many explorers, developers, and producers hire external </span><stro=
ng>Drilling Contractors</strong><span> to dig holes, collect samples, and d=
ig the mine. </span><strong>Mining Consultants</strong><span> assist with g=
eology, planning, environmental management and feasibility studies. </span>=
<strong>Mining Equipment Manufacturers</strong><span> like Caterpillar and =
Komatsu make the drills, excavators, haul trucks, and processing plants. Th=
ere are even dedicated </span><strong>Explosives Suppliers</strong><span> l=
ike Orica and Dyno Nobel that provide the explosives and blasting services =
necessary to go deep or through hard rock. Software providers, environmenta=
l and social impact assessment consultants, waste management companies, log=
istics and transportation providers, and mining safety and training provide=
rs all support the effort.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 5=
5); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But in terms o=
f actually finding new deposits and getting them out of the ground and into=
