font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0=
=2E625em 0; position: relative;"><stron=
g>Paydirt&#160;</strong></h3><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;"><span>Most explorers are lucky if they make one good discovery in=
 their lifetime. Two is excellent. Over the past year, Earth AI has made </=
span><strong>three</strong><span>: one wholly-owned Molybdenum deposit and =
two via Exploration Alliances.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 5=
5, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>Wi=
llow Glen: Molybdenum</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The first time Roman vi=
sited Willow Glen and looked at the data, he thought to himself: &#8220;The=
re&#8217;s this tiny old bit of Moly, I might drill that.&#8221;&#160;</p><=
p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;">But drilling is expensive and time-consuming, and money do=
esn&#8217;t grow on trees (although it may flow out of mines), and that&#82=
17;s just not how the industry works. You need to be meticulous. So Earth A=
I did more surveying at Willow Glen, got distracted, started thinking about=
 drilling for Tungsten or Copper, spent a year crossing t&#8217;s and dotti=
ng i&#8217;s, before all of the signs pointed back to that tiny old bit of =
Moly.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">When they drilled the site late in 2023, t=
hey learned that the model (and Roman&#8217;s gut) were right. The samples =
they drilled showed Molybdenum roughly 2x higher grade (0.3% vs. 0.16%) tha=
n the world&#8217;s leading Moly mines.&#160;</p><div class=3D"captioned-im=
