font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0=
=2E625em 0; position: relative;"><stron=
g>The Biotech Platform Business Model<=
/strong></h3><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-heig=
ht: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Earth AI&#8217;s business model is admittedl=
y not as clean to analyze as a SaaS model. Selling sticky, high-margin soft=
ware is good business if you can get it, but in many legacy, physical-world=
 industries, software isn&#8217;t the lever on progress that a vertically-i=
ntegrated business can be. Fortunately for Earth AI, by being forced to piv=
ot away from SaaS, I think they discovered a much more cash-generative busi=
ness model, one that looks a lot like a biotech platform.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;"><span>Last weekend, Elliot wrote an excellent piece on biotech pl=
atforms that he titled </span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/=
c86dee09-d278-4179-a68d-03f416876d61?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNu=
aMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-dec=
oration: underline;">Compounding Until Inflection</a></em><span>.&#160;</sp=
an></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26=
px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>&#8220;All value comes from clinical product=
s,&#8221; he writes, &#8220;</span><strong>But it&#8217;s only possible to =
build a generational biotech company with a foundational technology platfor=
m capable of developing multiple products.&#8221; </strong><span>Within pla=
tforms, the biotech companies that have held onto their assets instead of p=
artnering them away to big pharma have performed better in the market to da=
te, but Elliot argues that platform companies whose value compounds with mo=
re data can actually benefit from partnering in the long-term.&#160;</span>=
</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The logic goes like this:&#160;</p><ul style=3D"margi=
n-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-forma=
t: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); fon=
t-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left:=
 4px;">Partnerships &#8211; in which a platform sells a piece of its drug t=
o a large pharma company and develops it with them &#8211; cap upside but g=
enerate short-term cash flow and data.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8=
px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-bo=
x; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; m=
argin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">The cash allows the platform to a) sur=
vive and b) explore more assets.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0=
 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; col=
or: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-=
bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">The data allows the platform to improve the =
core technology and increase the odds of spitting off more and better asset=
s in the future.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-speci=
al-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, =
55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; paddi=
ng-left: 4px;">As the platform builds up a warchest and its technology via =
partnerships, it reaches a point at which it can develop more valuable prog=
rams in the future, fund their development, and retain ownership, creating =
more long-term value for the business.&#160;</p></li></ul><p style=3D"color=
: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"=
>The platform gets paid to compound until it hits an inflection point.&#160=
;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I see a lot of similarities between that model and w=
hat Earth AI is doing.&#160;</p><h3 class=3D"header-with-anchor-widget" sty=
le=3D"-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility; -moz-osx-font-smoothing: antiali=
ased; -webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility; -webkit-font-smoothing: antia=
liased; appearance: optimizelegibility; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-family=
: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system-headline, system-ui, -apple-system, Blink=
MacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Col=
or Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-we=
ight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0; position: relativ=
e;"><strong>Earth AI&#8217;s Business Model</strong></h3><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
Like any platform biotech company, Earth AI has developed technology that i=
t uses to discover and validate new assets better than incumbents can. Toda=
y, it can monetize those assets in a couple of main ways:</p><ol style=3D"m=
argin-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"=
box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-heigh=
t: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>Ownership=
:</strong><span> Earth AI can own and develop assets until they&#8217;re va=
luable to sell. For now, this could be as early as mid-feasibility (~ 20% s=
take for $10M) or as late as post-feasibility (~ 80% stake for $400M - $2B)=
=2E&#160;</span></p></li><li style=3D"m=
argin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-=
sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>Exploration A=
lliances:</strong><span> Like a pharma partnership, partner explorers cover=
 Earth AI&#8217;s costs, and Earth AI receives a 2-3% royalty. Earth AI is =
paid to learn, and receives pure margin cash flows when they&#8217;re succe=
ssful. The partner can choose to buy 1% of its royalty back for $2.5M withi=
n one year of discovery.&#160;</span></p></li></ol><p style=3D"color: rgb(5=
4, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Today,=
 Earth AI is pursuing both models. Exploration Alliance partners are essent=
ially paying for the company to learn, collect data, and refine the discove=
r/drill process that is its core IP. At Willow Glen, the company is funding=
 its own drilling costs in exchange for more ownership, and with each succe=
ssful drill, the value it can capture from a downstream developer or produc=
er increases.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Like pharma, the cash flows from t=
he assets that Earth AI discovers are protected &#8211; in the case of phar=
ma, by patents, and in the case of Earth AI, by mineral rights granted by t=
he state. Once it discovers a deposit, it owns the deposit, and can either =
generate revenue from it or sell its rights to a larger player. Unlike SaaS=
, a competitor can&#8217;t simply plop down on one of its existing sites an=
d try to outcompete it.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Over time, Earth AI will=
 build up a portfolio of revenue streams in addition to chunky cash payment=
s while growing its data set and getting more reps on its discover/drill pr=
ocess. It can reinvest the cash it generates into more drilling rigs, which=
 will allow it to crank the machine more quickly, and into owning more whol=
ly-owned projects that it can carry further through the development process=
=2E Eventually, it may even attempt to=20=
use its growing balance sheet to mine=20=
its own deposits.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Right now, all of this cash ge=
neration lives in the future. I believe that Earth AI is in a critical two-=
year period during which the key constraint will be capital.&#160;</p><p st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: =
0 0 20px 0;">If a single-asset biotech fails Phase I trials, the company is=
 essentially dead. If Earth AI fails feasibility at Willow Glen, it will be=
 a setback but not a deathblow given its live Exploration Alliances and abi=
lity to discover new deposits, assuming it has the capital to do so. Given =
the three successful drills, failing feasibility seems unlikely, but feasib=
ility takes time. (And even unsuccessful deposits can be sold for $1-5 mill=
ion, recouping costs).</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>But capital is important,=
 because </span><strong>capital buys speed</strong><span>.&#160;</span></p>=
<p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;">With more capital, Earth AI can buy more drills, speed up=
 feasibility at Willow Glen, begin drilling new targets, and expand its foo=
tprint to new deposits while it awaits results. Without it, it will be a wa=
iting game. But in either case, given that the company may be able to sell =
a stake in the project mid-feasibility, Earth AI should still be able to sp=
in the machine, it&#8217;s just a matter of pace.&#160;</p><p style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
">I&#8217;ve tried to construct a case in which Earth AI just fails, but gi=
ven their recent progress and the number of options they have, it seems unl=
ikely. Of course, there&#8217;s always that possibility. The biggest existe=
ntial threats might be that commodities markets sag, making developers and =
producers less likely to acquire mines, that Earth AI isn&#8217;t able to s=
uccessfully navigate the sales process, or that all of the positive early r=
esults happened to be flukes. They still need to be proven feasible.&#160;<=
/p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But the more I dig into the business, the more excited=
 I get. The downside seems protected and the upside, well, let&#8217;s look=
 at the numbers.&#160;</p><h3 class=3D"header-with-anchor-widget" style=3D"=
